> Does this fix all bugs of "not enough imports" so far? (In any case, looks like useful progress.)

I am not sure: I found these bugs by converting the command into a linter and bulk-processing a lot of mathlib files.  However, in the conversion, I still do not know how to handle in the linter the "nameless `instance`" issue.  So, the *linter* still shows differences, but I am not sure what would happen if I actually tested the *command* in bulk.

EDIT: actually, even though the nameless instance is not fixed in the *linter*, the current fixes do produce *much* better results with the linter anyway!
